description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Admin &amp; Clerical support to work across the Pathology Directorate at the Royal Cornwall Hospital, Truro.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Directorate is midway through the launch of a new quality, patient focused and exciting phase of change which will continue with the implementation of new analytical equipment in a refurbished laboratory, linked to a recent re-procurement of an existing managed laboratory service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job purpose is to provide support business, quality and improvement activities across all departments as part of the Pathology Business Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is desirable that the successful candidate/s have had recent experience of working within a similar role. They will have good keyboard skills, excellent interpersonal skills, clerical/admin experience and be confident using MS office products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pathology at RCH encompasses Clinical Chemistry, Haematology, Blood transfusion, Clinical Microbiology, Histopathology, mortuary services and phlebotomy. It has approximately 200 staff (clinical, scientific and support), an annual revenue budget of c£18m and reports around 9 million tests p.a.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A video about Pathology services in Truro is available at:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;youtube.com/watch?v=98ZA6hm7XBg&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further information is available on our website at:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;royalcornwall.nhs.uk/services/pathology/&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adrian Caley- Pathology Business Unit Manager, 07584155886 or adrian.caley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
